The paper discusses the issue of errors in spreadsheet development, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). It also focuses on the cognitive aspect of spreadsheet development, specifically overconfidence, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for testing and manipulation, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of reducing overconfidence on spreadsheet development, which could be relevant to computer engineering (cs.CE).
